description: Details of reserved matters of Phase 2B detailing 'appearance' and 'landscaping' for the construction of three terraces of 28 three-storey houses (22 x three-bedroom and 6 x four-bedroom units) and three apartment buildings varying in height between four-storeys high and part five, six, seven and eight-storeys high providing 184 flats (82 x one-bedroom; 88 x two bedroom; 14 x three-bedroom units) and a site management office of 62 sq. m (GIA) floor space; 34 car parking spaces located within an under croft car parking area; 102 on-street car parking spaces within Singapore Road, Talbot Road and new streets constructed as part the development; cycle and refuse stores; landscaping and public realm works  in pursuance of conditions 2 and 3 of Outline Planning Permission ref: P/2010/0419 dated: 29/09/2010 (and material amendment application ref: P/2013/1886, dated 19/08/2013) for 'Outline planning application seeking approval of layout, scale and access for the redevelopment of the Green Man Lane Estate comprising the demolition of the multi-storey car park and surface car parking areas, Dean Hall and the existing housing stock (464 homes) and the erection of  706 new residential units and houses (to comprise a net gain of  242 dwellings) together with new and altered roads, car and cycle parking, an energy centre, public and private open space and the provision of a gym, cafe, community floor space and enterprise units'.
decision_conditions: The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans and documents:  Drawings: L-90-001 A (in relation to the landscape proposals for Phase 2 only), 002 A, 003 A, 004 A, 005 A, 006 A, 007 A, 008 A, 009, 010, 300; 2236B Drawing P-003 A, P-004 A, P-005 A, P-006, P-007, P-008, P-009, P-010, P-011, P-012, P-013, P-014, P-015, P-016, P-017, P-018, P-019, P-020 A, P-021, P-022, P-023, P-024 A, P-025, P-026, P-027, P-028, P-029, P-030, P-031, P-032, P-033, P-100, P-101, P-102, P-103, P-110 B Proposed Site Plan; 056.0041-2100 P3, 2101 P3, 2110 P3, 2200 P1, 2201 P1, 2202 P3, 2210 P1, 2211 P1, 3100 P1.  Documents: Site specific arboricultural method statement (ref: D2205131603), dated 19.08.2014v6, prepared by Marishal Thompson Group and accompanying drawing L-90-005 Rev A, prepared by Broadway Malyan; Landscape & Open Space Strategy ref: 29419_1800_001 and Play Strategy ref: 29419_1800_002, dated June 2013, prepared by Broadway Malyan; Design & Access Statement, dated June 2013, prepared by Conran + Partners, Code for Sustainable Homes; Design Stage Pre-Assessment Report (ref: D126595) dated 27/01/2010; Email dated 21/08/2013 prepared by Ms M Scott (on behalf of Savills) regarding 'Comparison between approved tree removal'.  Reason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interest of proper planning. | Prior to first occupation of new dwelling F2.0.01 (as indicated on 2236B Drawing P-004 A), the temporary energy centre currently located within the rear garden of this new dwelling shall be removed and the rear garden shall be landscaped in accordance with the approved drawings.  Reason: In the interests of the amenity of the future occupiers of the relevant dwelling, in accordance with policies 3.5 of the London Plan 2011; 4.1 and 5.5 of Ealing's UDP 2004; and policies 7A, 7B and Local variation to policy 3.5 of Ealing's draft Development Management DPD. | Notwithstanding the approved plans, a minimum of five of the 46 replacement trees within the streetscape (Singapore Road, Williams Road, Tewkesbury Road) and / or civic area (Community CafT Plaza) as illustrated on drawing ref: L-90-008 A, shall be provided at a girth of between 50cm and 100cm. All the 46 replacement trees shall be planted during the first planting season following practical completion of the development hereby approved.  The tree planting shall have a two year maintenance / watering provision following planting and any trees which are removed, die, become severely damaged or diseased within five years of completion of the development shall be replaced with the same species or an approved alternative to the satisfaction of the Local Planning Authority within the next planting season.  Reason:  In the interest of biodiversity, sustainability, and to ensure that a satisfactory standard of visual amenity is provided and maintained in accordance with policies: 5.10, 7.1, 7.4, 7.5, 7.19 and 7.21 of the London Plan 2011, policy 1.1(j) of the adopted Ealing Development (or Core) Strategy 2012; policies 4.1, 4.5 and 5.5 of Ealing's adopted UDP 2004; and Ealing local variation to policy 5.10 of Ealing's draft Development Management DPD.
